lol may lead to benefits in heart failure patients.[A182603]', 'Nebivolol is a selective beta-1 adrenergic receptor antagonist that decreases vascular resistance, increases stroke volume and cardiac output, and does not negatively affect left ventricular function.[A182579,A182585] It has a long duration of action as effects can be seen 48 hours after stopping the medication and a wide therapeutic window as patients generally take 5-40mg daily.[A182579,L7985] Patients should not abruptly stop taking this medication as this may lead to exacerbation of coronary artery disease.[L7985] Diabetic patients should monitor their blood glucose levels as beta blockers may mask signs of hypoglycemia.[L7985]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
